==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mythical
<hw>Myth"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>mythicus</ets>, Gr. <?/. See
<er>Myth</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or relating to myths; described in a myth;
of the nature of a myth; fabulous; imaginary; fanciful;
mythological.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Myth"ic*al*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>mythic</qex> turf where danced the nymphs.</q>
<rj><qau>Mrs. Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hengist and Horsa, Vortigern and Rowena, Arthur and Mordred, are
<qex>mythical</qex> persons, whose very existence may be questioned.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mythographer</ent>⟦br⟧
